        {
          "id": "N_INTERLOCK_DONE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "So: the training-date interlock.\n\nIt\u2019s upstream of access/enable, and it refuses to interpret your situation generously.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_INTERLOCK"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_INTERLOCK",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "TALK_COMPLIANCE_3",
              "text": "Talk: Call the listed contact about training currency",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_3",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_DIAL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A phone number is printed in the corner with the confidence of a signature. You dial.\nAfter three tones, someone picks up like they were already speaking.",
          "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "Before you say anything: if this is about the training date, it is not \u201cexpired.\u201d\n\u201cExpired\u201d implies it was valid for a duration we agreed on. We never agreed on that.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_COMPLIANCE"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CALL_COMPLIANCE",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_OUT_OF_RANGE",
              "text": "Ask: The panel says \u201cout of range.\u201d",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_RANGE"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_FIX",
              "text": "Ask: What fixes it?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_FIX"
            },
            {
              "id": "PERSUADE_POLICY",
              "text": "Persuade: Give me the policy window and who can authorize an update.",
              "verb": "persuade",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PERSUADE",
                  "dc": 12
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_END_CALL",
              "text": "Leave: End call",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_HANGUP"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_RANGE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "Correct. \u201cRange\u201d is the safe word we use when Legal is in the room.\nYour training record has a date. The interlock reads the date.\nThe date does not match the current approved date window for work that could be interpreted as\u2014\nI\u2019m not saying you\u2019re doing it. I\u2019m saying the interlock can\u2019t know your heart.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_COMPLIANCE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_FIX",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "Officially? A training update, processed, posted, and ingested by the interlock system.\nUnofficially? I am not allowed to have unofficially.\n\nAlso, do not write \u201cI needed access.\u201d Write \u201caccess required by closure checklist.\u201d That phrasing holds up better.",
          "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "Policy Rev 7B defines the window; it\u2019s not a calendar concept, it\u2019s a risk classification concept.\nAuthorization is routed through Records for changes that touch interlock ingestion.\nIf you quote me: quote the document, not my mouth.",
          "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "No. If I say the window out loud, it becomes advice.\nYou want the policy text. You do not want me.",
          "next": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_COMPLIANCE_HANGUP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The line stays open half a second too long, like they\u2019re waiting to be quoted.\nThen it ends decisively, as if you dialed them by mistake.",
          "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOTO_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A steel hasp assembly is bolted to a main disconnect enclosure.\nPadlocks hang in layers. Tags overlap. Some are new. Some look like they were printed by a different century.\n\nA header placard reads: \u201cLOTO IS PERSONAL. NO EXCEPTIONS.\u201d\nSomeone has underlined \u201cPERSONAL\u201d hard enough to tear the laminate. It feels recent.",
          "next": "PC_LOTO_OPTIONS"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_LOTO_OPTIONS",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_COUNT",
              "text": "Ask: Count the locks.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_LOTO_COUNT"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_OWNERSHIP",
              "text": "Ask: Who owns the blank tags?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_LOTO_BLANKS"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_SAFETY",
              "text": "Talk: Call about LOTO log ownership",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOTO_COUNT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There are more locks than names you recognize.\nTwo tags are OLEA. One is a contractor you\u2019ve never heard of. One is blank except for a date that\u2019s been rewritten twice.",
          "next": "PC_LOTO_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOTO_BLANKS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A secondary tag clipped to the hasp says: \u201cUNASSIGNED TAGS ARE STILL ASSIGNED.\u201d\nIt includes a reference number and a promise that a log exists somewhere.",
          "next": "PC_LOTO_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_LOTO_POST",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_SUMMARY",
              "text": "Ask: Summarize the barrier.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_LOTO_DONE"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_SAFETY_2",
              "text": "Talk: Call about LOTO log ownership",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_2",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_LOTO_DONE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "So: LOTO requirements.\n\nThe disconnect handle is physically blocked, and any progress requires personal lock discipline and a verified zero-energy state\u2014without interpreting paperwork gaps as permission.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_LOTO"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_LOTO",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "TALK_SAFETY_3",
              "text": "Talk: Call about LOTO log ownership",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_3",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_DIAL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You dial the second number on the placard, the one printed smaller as if embarrassed.",
          "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_SAFETY_COORD",
          "text": "If you\u2019re calling to ask who put a lock on: I don\u2019t answer \u201cwho.\u201d\nI answer \u201cunder what work authorization,\u201d which is safer for everyone involved, including you.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_SAFETY"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CALL_SAFETY",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_AUTH",
              "text": "Ask: Under what authorization are these locks?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_AUTH"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_PROCEED",
              "text": "Ask: I need to proceed.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_NEED"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_LOG_REF_OLEA",
              "text": "Ask: I\u2019m OLEA. Give me the log reference number for the unassigned tags.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "player.factions",
                  "op": "in",
                  "value": "OLEA"
                }
              ],
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_REF"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_END_CALL",
              "text": "Leave: End call",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_HANGUP"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_AUTH",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_SAFETY_COORD",
          "text": "Several. Potentially overlapping. That\u2019s not an error. That\u2019s layered protection.\nThe blank tag\u2014before you say it\u2014might not be blank. Ink fades. Responsibility does not.\nAnd no, you cannot remove any lock that is not yours.\nEven if the person is retired, relocated, or\u2026 administratively unavailable.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_SAFETY"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_NEED",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_SAFETY_COORD",
          "text": "You need to document that you cannot proceed.\nDifferent need. Better outcome.\nPut your personal lock on when you get to that step, verify zero energy state per procedure, and do not interpret silence as permission.",
          "next": "N_CALL_SAFETY_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_REF",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_SAFETY_COORD",
          "text": "Write this down: you\u2019re looking for the lock-tree log tied to the hasp reference on the secondary tag.\nIf you quote me, I will deny I gave it to you and then point you to the placard that already did.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_SAFETY"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_SAFETY_HANGUP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "They exhale like they\u2019ve been holding that sentence for months.\nThe lock tree stays exactly as it is, which is the only outcome it permits.",
          "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_VENT_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The indicator is mounted at eye level, behind a sealed lens that has been cleaned in a tight circle, as if clarity is allowed only where needed.\nA simple legend: GREEN = NORMAL, AMBER = PURGE, RED = RESTRICTED.\n\nThe light is amber. The word \u201cPURGE\u201d has been relabeled once with a printed sticker that doesn\u2019t quite fit.",
          "next": "PC_VENT_OPTIONS"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_VENT_OPTIONS",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_BLOCKS",
              "text": "Ask: What does amber block?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_VENT_BLOCKS"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_WHY",
              "text": "Ask: Why is it purging?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_VENT_WHY"
            },
            {
              "id": "USE_TEST",
              "text": "Use: Press TEST",
              "verb": "use",
              "next": "N_VENT_TEST"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_FACILITIES",
              "text": "Talk: Call about ventilation states",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_VENT_BLOCKS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A nearby placard states: \u201cNO ACCESS BEYOND THIS POINT UNLESS VENTILATION = NORMAL AND LOTO VERIFIED.\u201d\nIt is signed by nobody and initialed by someone.",
          "next": "PC_VENT_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_VENT_WHY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A smaller note, typed and taped like an apology: \u201cPURGE MAY INDICATE SENSOR SELF-TEST. DO NOT ASSUME AIRFLOW.\u201d\nThe note is dated five years ago. The tape is newer.",
          "next": "PC_VENT_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_VENT_TEST",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You lift the cover. The tamper strip cracks with a sound that will definitely be discussed later.\nYou press TEST.\n\nNothing changes. A tiny indicator next to the button lights: \u201cINTERLOCK INHIBIT.\u201d\n\nInterlock\u2019s upstream.",
          "next": "PC_VENT_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_VENT_POST",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_SUMMARY",
              "text": "Ask: Summarize the barrier.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_VENT_DONE"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_FACILITIES_2",
              "text": "Talk: Call about ventilation states",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_2",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_VENT_DONE",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "So: a ventilation status dependency.\n\nAccess/verification steps are conditioned on NORMAL, but the indicator itself can be inhibited by upstream interlock logic.",
          "next": "PC_AFTER_VENT"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_AFTER_VENT",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "TALK_FACILITIES_3",
              "text": "Talk: Call about ventilation states",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_DIAL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK_3",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_DIAL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You dial. The phone answers on the first ring, like it was waiting to be blamed.",
          "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "Amber is not \u201cpurging.\u201d\nAmber is \u201cpurge state indicated.\u201d There is a difference.\nOne is a verb. One is a liability.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_FACILITIES"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CALL_FACILITIES",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_MAKES_AMBER",
              "text": "Ask: What makes it amber?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_AMBER"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_CLEAR",
              "text": "Ask: Can you clear it?",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_CLEAR"
            },
            {
              "id": "PERSUADE_REFRESH",
              "text": "Persuade: Log a status refresh request anyway and tell me the ticket ID.",
              "verb": "persuade",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PERSUADE",
                  "dc": 10
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_END_CALL",
              "text": "Leave: End call",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_HANGUP"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_AMBER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "It can be airflow. It can be sensor health. It can be the system refusing to commit to a claim.\nWhich, frankly, I respect.\nAlso, if you pressed the test button, that\u2019s fine, but you\u2019ve now created a tamper event.\nNot a safety event. A tamper event. Those are tracked more aggressively.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_FACILITIES"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_CLEAR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "I can\u2019t \u201cclear\u201d reality. I can request a status refresh.\nBut the refresh is inhibited by the access interlock, because the system assumes only trained personnel request refreshes.\nDon\u2019t ask me why it assumes that; I didn\u2019t raise it.",
          "next": "PC_CALL_FACILITIES"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "Fine. I\u2019ll file the refresh request as \u201cstatus verification pending access inhibit.\u201d\nIf anyone asks: you did not ask me to bypass anything. You asked me to document.\nNo ticket number over the phone. The system will generate it in Records view.",
          "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "No. If I create a paper trail that implies action, it becomes action.\nDocument your constraint. That\u2019s the only safe verb here.",
          "next": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_HANGUP"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CALL_FACILITIES_HANGUP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The amber light keeps shining with the calm certainty of a warning nobody owns.",
          "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAC_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A metal rack holds laminated placards, each one numbered, each one revised, each one contradicting the next like a committee argument preserved in plastic.\n\nPlacard 1: \u201cVERIFY TRAINING CURRENCY PRIOR TO ENABLE.\u201d\nPlacard 2: \u201cAPPLY PERSONAL LOTO PRIOR TO ENTRY.\u201d\nPlacard 3: \u201cCONFIRM VENTILATION NORMAL PRIOR TO LOTO VERIFICATION.\u201d\nPlacard 4: \u201cIF VENTILATION NOT NORMAL, INITIATE PURGE USING ENABLED CONTROLS.\u201d\n\nA final placard sits behind the rest, less handled:\n\u201cIF REQUIREMENTS CONFLICT, STOP AND DOCUMENT CONSTRAINTS. DO NOT RESOLVE VIA ASSUMPTION.\u201d",
          "next": "PC_PLAC_POST"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_PLAC_POST",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "ASK_LOOP",
              "text": "Ask: That\u2019s a loop.",
              "verb": "ask",
              "next": "N_PLAC_LOOP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_PLAC_LOOP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "It doesn\u2019t resolve by action. It resolves by definition.\n\nThe stack does not provide a pen. It assumes you brought one, or someone else did.",
          "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CONTACTS_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There are multiple numbers, each promising authority. None promising help.\n\nNo one answers \u201cWho owns this corridor?\u201d out loud.\nPick a number: Compliance Desk, Safety Coordinator, or Facilities Operator.",
          "next": "PC_CONTACTS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_CONTACTS_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "TALK_COMP",
              "text": "Talk: Compliance Desk",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CONTACT_COMP"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_SAFETY",
              "text": "Talk: Safety Coordinator",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CONTACT_SAFETY"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_FAC",
              "text": "Talk: Facilities Operator",
              "verb": "talk",
              "next": "N_CONTACT_FAC"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CONTACT_COMP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_COMPLIANCE_DESK",
          "text": "Ownership is a legal category. Physically, it\u2019s a hallway.\nProcedurally, it\u2019s a boundary.\nIf you need a single name, you want Records, not me.",
          "next": "PC_CONTACTS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CONTACT_SAFETY",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_SAFETY_COORD",
          "text": "\u201cOwns\u201d is a dangerous verb. I \u201cmaintain oversight.\u201d\nOversight does not include removing locks, authorizing entry, or being present when things go wrong.",
          "next": "PC_CONTACTS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_CONTACT_FAC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NPC_FACILITIES_OP",
          "text": "I own the ventilation readings the same way a thermometer owns a fever.",
          "next": "PC_CONTACTS_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMMIT_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Between the interlock, the lock point, and the ventilation indicator, the corridor has the shape of a closed fist.\n\nIt doesn\u2019t stop you by force. It stops you by making every next step require a previous step you cannot take.",
          "next": "PC_COMMIT"
        },
        {
          "id": "PC_COMMIT",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "GIVE_LOG",
              "text": "Give: Record \u201cThree main ops barriers\u201d in your closure notes",
              "verb": "give",
              "next": "N_COMMIT_WRITEUP"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "Leave: Back",
              "verb": "leave",
              "next": "R_BACK_TO_MENU"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N_COMMIT_WRITEUP",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You write it in the only language that survives audits:\n\n- Training-date interlock blocks enable/access.\n- LOTO requirements prevent manipulation without personal lock and verified zero-energy state.\n- Ventilation status dependency requires NORMAL before access/verification steps, and the indicator is inhibited by the interlock.\n\nYour handwriting stays steady. Your jaw doesn\u2019t. That counts as composure.",
          "next": "END_OPS_BARRIERS_IDENTIFIED"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_OPS_BARRIERS_IDENTIFIED",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "ops_barriers_identified",
